\title{Ring of polynomials is a module}
\author{alex-nelson}
\import{notation}
\date{2025-12-19}
\taxon{example}

\p{Let #{R} be a [[ra-0003]], let #{x} be a formal variable. Then the [ring of polynomials](ra-000L) #{R[x]} is a module over #{R}.}

\p{\textbf{Proof idea:} We see that #{R[x]} is closed under addition, and it's closed under scalar multiplication.}